{
  "texts": [
    "For example, cluster 2CT+ (CTCTCT or AGA-GAG in reverse complementary orientation) features EPMs with at least two or more (+) cytosine-thymine dimers.",
    "Of the now 18 different clusters, we identified 15 clusters that have at least one EPM with significant similarities to a TFBS in the JASPAR2020 DB (p value <0.001 and e-value <0.01) 24 (Fig. 4c and Supplementary Data 4).",
    "Interestingly, we identified 26 different TFBS in twelve clusters (2CT+, CGNCGT, WAAMAW, 2GCB+, GSRGV, 2CWY, TNNGCCS, 5W+, YACA, TCTGW, CTAG and 3SSN) that have a very high similarity of 95% measured with Pearson correlation coefficient (PCC).",
    "Of these TFBSs, eleven are solely matching to EPMs from the SSR leaf models, compared to seven from the MSR, and nine shared ones.",
    "This does indicate that the leaf SSR models perform slightly better on the identification of putative TFBSs."
  ]
}